This paper discusses the use of SDN-based routing approaches in networks with middleboxes, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also addresses resource constraints and traversal constraints, which are common issues in network security (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed solution involves the use of algorithms and simulations, which are related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed solution, which is relevant to computer architecture (cs.AR).
